{
    "_readme": "COMMON layer for DynamicAIB - map-agnostic scaffolding merged into EVERY map's flat DynamicAIB.json by Build-AIBandits.ps1. NEVER put coordinates here (those are per-map, under ../maps/<mission>/). THE MODEL: bandits are defined GLOBALLY here and only PLACED per-map. Three global tiers, each referenced by name from a per-map file: (1) 'loadouts' = clothing+loot kits; (2) 'groupTemplates' = fully-defined reusable squads (which loadout, weapon, size, accuracy, grenadechance, dog, faction) - a per-map group can just say {\"template\":\"roadblock\",\"waypoints\":[...]} and inherit everything, overriding any field inline; (3) 'sniperTemplates' = reusable SVD nests a per-map file places with {\"template\":\"svd_nest\",\"positions\":[...],\"triggerpos\":\"...\"}. Edit a kit/template ONCE here and every map inherits it. 'loadouts.<name>.classes' is the NPC-class pool a group draws from (cycled to reach 'size'). 'npcproperties' is the clothing/loot kit; every clothing slot is a POOL the mod picks ONE entry from per NPC, so multi-entry slots = visual variety across a group. LOOT DROPS PER-NPC AND IS MULTIPLIED BY GROUP SIZE. Despite the wiki calling it 'randomized' with 'repeat to raise the chance', in-game observation is that the WHOLE array drops on each NPC and repeated entries pile into STACKS - so a 14-item array on a size-8 squad = ~112 items on the ground (stacks of morphine, rags, etc). Therefore KEEP LOOT ARRAYS TINY (2-4 low-value, thematic items) and NEVER repeat a valuable. Variety comes from the CLOTHING pools (one per slot per NPC), NOT from padding loot. Also: the NPC's whole WORN kit (clothes, vest, backpack, gun + its attachments/mag) always drops on death - that is the bulk of a corpse's value and is governed by the loadout/weapon, not the loot array. NOTE: the loot array takes classnames only - there is NO condition/health field, so 'sometimes ruined/damaged' drops cannot be scripted here. Loadout kits (consolidated): military (rich, all-purpose AKM bandit - absorbs the old biker-gang 'raider' look), military_heavy (rich, top tier), town (rich civ) - these three carry the full clothing/loot variety; pistol + melee stay deliberately MINIMAL (scavenger/desperate); raider_m4 (M4 airfield specialist) + sniper (SVD). Clothing/weapon/loot classnames are vanilla DayZ and can drift between game versions - an invalid classname just means that item is absent on the NPC (not a crash), but worth a sanity pass.",
    "flags": {
        "_readme_useSpawnLocations": "Master AI-bandit spawn switch, read by Build-AIBandits.ps1 (NOT the mod - stripped from the composed flat file). 1 (default, also assumed if absent) = compose spawn placements normally. 0 = emit EMPTY Dynamic + Static files (no bandits, effectively no mod) while leaving every authored placement intact - fully reversible. Editable in the Server Files UI as the 'Aib-common' item; the mod stays loaded (unload it via deploy/mods.conf).",
        "useSpawnLocations": 1,
        "version": 2,
        "showtriggers": 0,
        "cleanzerovector": 0,
        "crashsitegroup": "Random",
        "cardamage": 1
    },
